Adjust oven rack to middle position and turn oven to broil. Mix butter and garlic powder in a small bowl. Place 6 slices of bread onto a foil-lined baking sheet. Sprinkle a portion of cheese over each slice. Top with the remaining 6 slices of bread. Brush tops with half the butter and sprinkle with half the oregano Broil sandwiches until golden brown, about 3 minutes. Remove pan from oven, flip sandwiches, brush the other sides with remaining butter and sprinkle with oregano. Return to oven and broil until golden, about 3 minutes longer. Cut sandwiches in half diagonally, and serve with vodka sauce on the side for dipping.